title: My device connected to B593s-931’s wireless network, but cannot open Web UI
answer:
1. Double![](http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=HtmlAreaImage&imageId=32655) to check your wireless network connection on windows start bar. Make sure your device is connected with your B593s-931 not other Wi-Fi device. 

 2.Open Web Browser from your device (ex. Microsoft Internet Explorer). Go *<u>http://192.168.1.1</u>* to open B593s-931’s Web UI. 

 ![](http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=HtmlAreaImage&imageId=32658) 

 3.If Web Browser failed to bring you to Web UI, click “Tool” from Browser then select “Internet Options”. 

 ![](http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=HtmlAreaImage&imageId=32656) 

 Select “Connections” tab, then click “LAN settings”. 

 ![](http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=HtmlAreaImage&imageId=32659) 

 For the “Local Area Network (LAN) Settings” pop-up, uncheck the top three check-boxes. Then click “OK” to apply changes. 

 ![](http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=HtmlAreaImage&imageId=32660)  

 Refresh the Web Browser to show B593s-931 management console page.
